    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2003 BMW M3 (E46) is a museum-grade example of the S54-powered legend. The 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six features individual throttle bodies and a recently serviced double-VANOS system, ensuring peak volumetric efficiency and razor-sharp throttle response up to the 8,000 RPM redline. Power is managed via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory-calibrated limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance is complete: the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced, and the rod bearings have been replaced with documented tolerances. The chassis remains perfectly true, retaining all original VIN tags and factory bushings. Finished in Carbon Black Metallic over Nappa leather, the exterior has undergone a full paint correction and ceramic coating. This is a turn-key collector piece with zero fluid seepage and perfect compression across all six cylinders.",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
